.TH ISATTY 3 2008-12-03 "Linux" "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
isatty \- test whether a gangbangin' file descriptor refers ta a terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <unistd.h>
.sp
.BI "int isatty(int " fd );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR isatty ()
function tests whether
.I fd
is a open file descriptor referrin ta a terminal.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR isatty ()
returns 1 if
.I fd
is a open file descriptor referrin ta a terminal;
otherwise 0 is returned, and
.I errno
is set ta indicate tha error.
.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B EBADF
.I fd
is not a valid file descriptor.
.TP
.B EINVAL
.I fd
refers ta a gangbangin' file other than a terminal.
POSIX.1-2001 specifies tha error
